translated: Holmquist, Bertil Ivan Daniel, vicar, Fridhemsberg, b. 3/5/07 in Lundby, Gothenburg and Bohus County, son of Ailfred H. and Berta f. Olsson. Married in 1938 to Martia Wänndahl, with children: Ingela and Sven b. 1940, Gudrun b. 1944, and Gunnar b. 1947. Education: graduated from high school in Vänersborg in 1930, fil. dr. in theology in 1933, ordained minister in 1937 after practical theology and ecclesiastical examinations. Worked as a curate in Angered, Torsby, and Lundby, later as a vicar and curate in Sjötofta, pastor and curate in Hunnestad, and pastoral assistant in Knäred, Kungsbacka, and Gamlestads parish in Gothenburg. Pastoral work includes work at Gothenburg's Poor Relief Agency and Renström Hospital from 1939, and as a vicar in Fagereds parish since 1945.
